  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>A Rendezvous by Cruise and Rail. Get to know the many faces of the province of Québec travelling by cruise ship and train along the magnificent St. Lawrence River. Your journey will showcase the best of this region starting off with a relaxing two-day cruise where you will sail slowly past historic sites and charming fishing villages, enjoy onboard gourmet meals and spend an afternoon whale watching in the heart of the stunning Saguenay-St. Lawrence Marine Park. Historic Québec City abounds with internationally renowned festivals and the free Cirque du Soleil show is not to be missed. Travel in comfort by train to the bustling city of Montreal for its vibrant Old Town, elegant boutiques and numerous museums and galleries. At night, join the locals for cocktails on terraces and dine in the city's countless restaurants. At the end of the tour continue on to the enchanting lake-side village of Mont Tremblant, for a few relaxing days in the mountains.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Return flights </strong>from the UK.</li>
<li><strong>All transfers </strong>between airport, hotel, cruise ship, railway stations.</li>
<li><strong>2 day St. Lawrence River cruise </strong>with English commentary and on board entertainment. Gratitudes for the crew.</li>
<li><strong>Business Class Rail Journey</strong> Québec City to Montreal with meals and beverages</li>
<li><strong>Daily hot &amp; cold breakfast. 2 lunches and 1 dinner on cruise days</strong></li>
<li><strong>Breakfast or lunch </strong>on train. 1 lunch in Tremblant.</li>
</ul>
<p>This tour operates without the services of an Inghams Representative. However you will be given contact details of the Inghams Office in Canada who will be able to assist you whenever required.</p>
<h3>Inghams Plus</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Early Booking Offer</strong> Save up to £160 per couple (book by 28 Feb 2013)</li>
<li><strong>Free </strong>Guided Walking Tour of Historic Quebec City</li>
<li><strong>Free </strong>Gondola ticket to enjoy panoramic views of Mont Tremblant and its lake</li>
<li><strong>Free </strong>lunch on the mountain in Mont Tremblant</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Montreal</strong> (3 Nights)<br />Marriot Springhill <strong>****</strong></li>
<li><strong>Québec City</strong><br />Fairmont Chateau Frontenac <strong>*****</strong> (1 Night) and Marriott Courtyard <strong>****</strong> (2 Nights)</li>
<li><strong>La Malbaie</strong> (1 Night)<br />Fairmont Le Manoir Richelieu <strong>*****</strong></li>
<li><strong>Mont Tremblant </strong>(4 Nights)<br />Fairmont Tremblant <strong>***** </strong>or Marriott Residence Inn <strong>****</strong></li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<h3>On Board the Cavalier Maxi</h3>
<p><strong>One of Canada’s leading river cruises</strong></p>
<p><strong>Facilities </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>2 terraces with magnificent viewpoints</li>
<li>Top deck with panoramic views</li>
<li>Bar and bistro</li>
<li>3 dining rooms</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Meals </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Meals included (freshly prepared on board): Daily hot &amp; cold full service breakfast with choice of items</li>
<li>Daily full service lunches with a choice of menu</li>
<li>Afternoon snacks of regional specialities on day 2</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Entertainment </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>English commentary at points of interest along the way</li>
<li>Poker and Black Jack games with prizes, even dance lessons!</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Size </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>57 metres long</li>
<li>500 passenger capacity</li>
</ul>
<h3>Highlights of your Tour &amp; Cruise</h3>
<p><strong>River Cruise</strong> A two day cruise along the St. Lawrence River with its amazing landscape, charming villages and historic sites.</p>
<p><strong>Whale Watching</strong> A chance to observe up to 13 different species of whale in their natural habitat in the world famous Saguenay– St. Lawrence Marine Park.</p>
<p><strong>Train</strong> Travel in style with a scenic business class rail journey from Quebec to Montreal, enjoying the views and your included meal and beverages.</p>
<p><strong>City Stays</strong> Visit historic Quebec City, a World Heritage Site, and vibrant Montreal.</p>
<p><strong>Mountains</strong> Four days of mountain relaxation and activities in the charming lakeside village of Mont Tremblant.</p>
<p><strong>Day 1-2 Montreal</strong> | Fly into Montreal and transfer to your hotel in the heart of the Old Town. Start your holiday exploring this vibrant city with its cobblestone streets, boutiques, galleries and famed restaurants and bars.</p>
<p><strong>Day 3 Montreal–Quebec City (Two Day Cruise)</strong> | Embark on your two-day cruise along the St. Lawrence River. Start the day with a hearty breakfast whilst watching the scenery unfold as you cruise by. Relax, read a book, or maybe join in some of the on board entertainment. English commentary on points of interest is provided. Lunch included. Late afternoon arrive in Quebec City and transfer <strong>to Hotel Fairmont Chateau Frontenac in the heart of Old Quebec, overlooking the river. Evening is at leisure, with time to stroll around and absorb the sounds and lights of the Old Town.<br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>Day 4 Quebec City–La Malbaie (Whale Watching) </strong>| Rejoin the cruise ship to continue your journey along the St.Lawrence River. Breakfast and lunch are served on board. After lunch arrive in the Saguenay–St. Lawrence Marine Park, home to 13 different species of whales, including the Blue and Beluga whale. Observe and photograph these fascinating mammals from the comfort of the observation deck before enjoying a snack of local specialities. Disembark the ship late afternoon for your transfer to your hotel. Dinner included.</p>
<p><strong>Day 5 La Malbaie–Quebec City</strong> | After a leisurely breakfast and maybe a swim in the hotel’s pool join the coach for the two hour ride to Quebec City. The afternoon is free for you to enjoy the city and explore its many historic sites and wonderful views. At night don’t miss out on the free outdoor Cirque du Soleil show. Accommodation for the next two nights is in the centrally located Marriott Courtyard hotel.</p>
<p><strong>Day 6 Quebec at Leisure</strong> | A full day to explore this World Heritage Site city. Join the free guided walking tour and sightseeing tour, or simply explore the narrow streets and browse the interesting boutiques and galleries. Relax on one of the many terrace cafes and enjoy dinner in the gourmet restaurants, followed by the Image Mill, an incredible al fresco sound and light show.</p>
<p><strong>Day 7 Quebec City – Montreal by Train </strong>| Join the train for a three hour ride to Montreal. Travelling in the comfort of business class simply sit-back and enjoy the scenery, Meal and beverages are included. The afternoon and evening are at leisure. Overnight at the Marriott Springhill hotel.</p>
<p><strong>Day 8 Montreal – Mont Tremblant </strong>| After a morning of sightseeing in Montreal,we will arrange your transfer to Tremblant.Your accommodation for the next four nights is in the Marriott Residence Inn or Fairmont Mont Tremblant both centrally located at the traffic free base of the mountain.</p>
<p><strong>Day 9-11 Mont Tremblant </strong>| This lakeshore village in the Laurentian Mountains combines European ambiance with Québecois hospitality. The quaint and picturesque buildings have not lost any of their old world charm and host numerous cafes, shops and fine dining restaurants. Mont Tremblant offers a wide range of activities including hiking, lake cruises, water sports, fishing, golf, cable car rides, float trips and rafting, spas, horseback riding and a casino. Make use of your FREE gondola ride for panoramic views over the resort and enjoy your FREE lunch on the mountain.</p>
<p><strong>Day 12 Mont Tremblant - UK</strong> | Afternoon departure to Montreal airport for your overnight flight to the UK.</p>]]></bodyText>
